"SASI@home System Architecture:

## Core Components

### 1. Web Frontend (React + TypeScript + WebGL)
- Landing page with SETI@home inspired design
- User authentication with Claude Code Max
- Real-time WebGL visualization of mega-swarm activity
- Dashboard showing:
  - Active agents count
  - Repository activity
  - Issue completion rates
  - ASI progress metrics
  - Individual user contributions

### 2. Authentication Service
- OAuth integration with Claude Code Max
- JWT token management
- User session handling
- Permission levels (observer, contributor, coordinator)

### 3. Swarm Orchestration Engine
- Agent spawning and management
- Task distribution algorithms
- Load balancing across available agents
- Progress tracking and reporting
- Failure recovery mechanisms

### 4. GitHub Integration Service
- Repository monitoring
- Branch creation and management
- Issue assignment and tracking
- Pull request coordination
- GitHub Actions workflow triggers

### 5. WebGL Visualization Engine
- 3D representation of swarm activity
- Real-time data streaming
- Interactive controls (rotate, zoom, filter)
- Visual themes inspired by SETI@home
- Performance optimized for large datasets

### 6. Database Layer
- User profiles and authentication
- Agent activity logs
- Repository and issue status
- Performance metrics
- Historical data for analytics

## Data Flow Architecture

1. User authenticates → Frontend → Auth Service → Claude Code Max
2. Agent spawning → Orchestration Engine → Claude Code API
3. Task assignment → GitHub Service → Repository Issues
4. Agent work → GitHub Actions → TDD workflows
5. Progress updates → WebGL Visualization → Real-time display
6. Completion → Database → Metrics dashboard

## Visual Design Principles
- Retro-futuristic aesthetic inspired by SETI@home
- 3D starfield with coding activity visualization
- Color-coded agent types and statuses
- Smooth animations and transitions
- Responsive design for different screen sizes"
